  "title": "Sr Mgr, TTR Ops & Process Engineering",
  "description": "<p>The Test Operations Excellence Organization have full supervision on:</p><p><em>All OSATs in APAC providing Probe, Final Test and Tape-&-Reel Services to Qorvo and</em></p><ul><li>Ensuring Customers Delivery Commitments and Qorvo Revenue Attainment</li><li>Meeting all Operational KPIs</li><li>Meeting Quality Standards </li><li>Supporting Customers’ Requirements </li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities / Accountabilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Work with QI Sourcing, Quality, Engineering & Planning to drive OSAT on all production delivery commitments to customers & Monthly LE & Quarterly Revenue attainment </li><li>Partner with Engineering team to evaluate & qualify OSAT Technology (NTI) for Qorvo New Production Introduction (NPI)as business continuity and future growth</li><li>Engage OSAT to get prepared and validate to ensure smooth transition from NPI to THVM readinesss for Key Programs </li><li>Manage OSATs and drive Performance Metrics such as OTD, CT, Probe, Test & TnR Yield, OEE, Track Utilization Percentage of Qorvo consigned assets </li><li>Engage with OSATs on Continuous Improvement Projects (TCPII) and be the liaison between Qorvo (QI / GATE / BU) & OSAT on key projects (POR/POA) success</li><li>Manage & ensure that OSATs comply with all Qorvo standards and commitments</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelors of Engineering or equivalent with at least 20 or more years of experience in similar capacity</li><li>Has at least 5 years of experience on managing operations in various Asia Pacific countries such as Malaysia, China, Korea and etc. </li><li>Has at least 5 years of experience on handling Infrastructure and Defense Products and Mobile Products processes</li><li>Has at least 15 years of engineering experience & familiar with Probe, Test Tape & Reel processes </li></ul>",
